'''Immunodermatology''' studies [[skin]] as an organ of [[Immunity (medical)|immunity]] in health and disease. Several areas have special attention, such as photo-immunology (effects of [[Ultraviolet|UV]] light on skin defense), [[inflammation|inflammatory]] diseases such as [[Hidradenitis suppurativa]], [[allergy|allergic]] contact [[dermatitis]] and [[atopic eczema]], presumably [[autoimmune]] skin diseases such as [[vitiligo]] and [[psoriasis]], and finally the [[immunology]] of [[microbial]] skin diseases such as [[retrovirus]] infections and [[leprosy]]. New therapies in development for the [[Immunosuppressant|immunomodulation]] of common immunological skin diseases include [[Biomolecule|biologicals]] aimed at neutralizing [[Tumor necrosis factor-alpha|TNF-alfa]] and [[chemokine receptor]] inhibitors.
